obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4505)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 5th July, 2004, vide notification No. G.S.R. 395(E), dated 2nd July, 2004, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4505&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Fiscal Responsibility`
  line `and Budget Management Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4506)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4506&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "fiscal deficit" means the excess of total disbursements, from the Consolidated Fund of India,`
  line `excluding repayment of debt, over total receipts into the Fund (excluding the debt receipts), during a`
  line `financial year;`
  line
  line `^1[^2[(aa) "Central Government debt" at any date means--`
  line
  line `(i) the total outstanding liabilities of the Central Government on the security of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of India, including external debt valued at current exchange rates;`
  line
  line `(ii) the total outstanding liabilities in the public account of India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such financial liabilities of any body corporate or other entity owned or controlled by`
  line `the Central Government, which the Government is to repay or service from the annual financial`
  line `statement, reduced by the cash balance available at the end of that date;]]`
  line
  line `(b) "fiscal indicators" means the measures such as numerical ceilings and proportions to gross`
  line `domestic product, as may be prescribed, for evaluation of the fiscal position of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `^1[^3[(bb) "general Government debt" means the sum total of the debt of the Central Government`
  line `and the State Governments, excluding inter-Governmental liabilities;]]`
  line
  line `^4[(bc) "gross domestic product" means the sum of the gross value added by all resident`
  line `production units plus that part of taxes, less subsidies, on products, which is not included in the`
  line `valuation of output, during a financial year, reckoned at current market prices, as published by the`
  line `Central Statistics Office from time to time;]`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4[(ca) "real gross domestic product" means gross domestic product, reckoned at constant prices,`
  line `as published by the Central Statistics Office from time to time;`
  line
  line `(cb) "real output growth" means growth in real gross domestic product;]`
  line
  line `(d) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 146 (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 211, for clause (aa) (w.e.f 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 211, ibid., for clause (bb) (w.e.f 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 211, ibid. (w.e.f 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Clauses (e) and (f) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 211 (w.e.f. 31-3-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4507)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Fiscal policy statements to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4507&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall lay in`
  line `each financial year before both Houses of Parliament the following statements of fiscal policy along with`
  line `the annual financial statement and ^1[demands for grants except the Medium-term Expenditure Framework`
  line `Statement,] namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Medium-term Fiscal Policy Statement;`
  line
  line `(b) the Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement;`
  line
  line `(c) the Macro-economic Framework Statement;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) the Medium-term Expenditure Framework Statement.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The statements referred to in clauses (a) to (c) of sub-section (1) shall be followed up with the`
  line `Medium-term Expenditure Framework Statement with detailed analysis of underlying assumptions.`
  line
  line `(1B) The Central Government shall lay the Medium-term Expenditure Framework Statement referred`
  line `to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) before both Houses of Parliament, immediately, following the session`
  line `of Parliament in which the policy statements referred to in clauses (a) to (c) were laid under sub-section`
  line `(1).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Medium-term Fiscal Policy Statement shall set forth a three-year rolling target for prescribed`
  line `fiscal indicators with specification of underlying assumptions.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular, and without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), the`
  line `Medium-term Fiscal Policy Statement shall include an assessment of sustainability relating to--`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(ii) the use of capital receipts including market borrowings for generating productive assets.`
  line
  line `(4) The Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement shall, inter alia, contain--`
  line
  line `(a) the policies of the Central Government for the ensuing financial year relating to taxation,`
  line `expenditure, market borrowings and other liabilities, lending and investments, pricing of administered`
  line `goods and services, securities and description of other activities such as underwriting and guarantees`
  line `which have potential budgetary implications;`
  line
  line `(b) the strategic priorities of the Central Government for the ensuing financial year in the fiscal`
  line area;
  line
  line `(c) the key fiscal measures and rationale for any major deviation in fiscal measures pertaining to`
  line `taxation, subsidy, expenditure, administered pricing and borrowings;`
  line
  line `(d) an evaluation as to how the current policies of the Central Government are in conformity with`
  line `the fiscal management principles set out in section 4 and the objectives set out in the Medium-term`
  line `Fiscal Policy Statement.`
  line
  line `(5) The Macro-economic Framework Statement shall contain an assessment of the growth prospects`
  line `of the economy with specification of underlying assumptions.`
  line
  line `(6) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions the Macroeconomic`
  line `Framework Statement shall contain an assessment relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the growth in the gross domestic product;`
  line
  line `(b) the fiscal balance of the Union Government as reflected in the ^4*** gross fiscal balance;`
  line
  line `(c) the external sector balance of the economy as reflected in the current account balance of the`
  line `balance of payments.`
  line
  line `^5[(6A) (a) The Medium-term Expenditure Framework Statement shall set forth a three-year rolling`
  line `target for prescribed expenditure indicators with specification of underlying assumptions and risk`
  line involved.
  line
  line `(b) In particular and without prejudice to the provisions contained in clause (a), the Medium-term`
  line `Expenditure Framework Statement shall, inter alia, contain--`
  line
  line `(i) the expenditure commitment of major policy changes involving new service, new`
  line `instruments of service, new schemes and programmes;`
  line
  line `(ii) the explicit contingent liabilities, which are in the form of stipulated annuity payments`
  line `over a multi-year time-frame;`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(7) The Medium-term Fiscal Policy Statement, ^7[the Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement, the Mediumterm`
  line `Expenditure Framework Statement] and the Macro-economic Framework Statement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be in such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 147, for "demand for grants" (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 147, ibid. (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Item (i) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 212 (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. The words "revenue balance and" omitted by s. 212, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2018)`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 147 (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Item (iii) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 212, (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 147, for "the Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement" (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4508)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Fiscal management principles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 213, for section 4 (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4508&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Fiscal management principles.--(1) The Central Government shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) take appropriate measures to limit the fiscal deficit upto three per cent. of gross domestic`
  line `product by the 31st March, 2021;`
  line
  line `(b) endeavour to ensure that--`
  line
  line `(i) the general Government debt does not exceed sixty per cent.;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Central Government debt does not exceed forty per cent.,`
  line
  line `of gross domestic product by the end of financial year 2024-2025;`
  line
  line `(c) not give additional guarantees with respect to any loan on security of the Consolidated Fund of`
  line `India in excess of one-half per cent. of gross domestic product, in any financial year;`
  line
  line `(d) endeavour to ensure that the fiscal targets specified in clauses (a) and (b) are not exceeded after`
  line `stipulated target dates.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall prescribe the annual targets for reduction of fiscal deficit for the`
  line `period beginning from the date of commencement of Part XV of Chapter VIII of the Finance Act, 2018 (13 of 2018),`
  line `and ending on the 31st March, 2021:`
  line
  line `Provided that exceeding annual fiscal deficit target due to ground or grounds of national security, act`
  line `of war, national calamity, collapse of agriculture severely affecting farm output and incomes, structural`
  line `reforms in the economy with unanticipated fiscal implications, decline in real output growth of a quarter`
  line `by at least three per cent. points below its average of the previous four quarters, may be allowed for the`
  line `purposes of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Any deviation from fiscal deficit target under sub-section (2) shall not exceed one-half per cent. of`
  line `the gross domestic product in a year.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, in case of increase in real output growth of a quarter by at least`
  line `three per cent. points above its average of the previous four quarters, reduce the fiscal deficit by at least`
  line `one-quarter per cent. of the gross domestic product in a year.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the fiscal deficit is allowed to vary from the target prescribed under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) or deviation is initiated under sub-section (4), a statement explaining the reasons thereof`
  line `and the path of return to annual prescribed targets under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be,`
  line `before both the Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4509)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Borrowing from Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4509&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall not borrow from the Reserve`
  line Bank.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may borrow from`
  line `the Reserve Bank by way of advances to meet temporary excess of cash disbursement over cash receipts`
  line `during any financial year in accordance with the agreements which may be entered into by that`
  line `Government with the Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that any advances made by the Reserve Bank to meet temporary excess cash disbursement`
  line `over cash receipts in any financial year shall be repayable in accordance with the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 17 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934(2 of 1934).`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank may subscribe to the`
  line `primary issues of Central Government Securities due to ground or grounds specified in the proviso to subsection`
  line `(2) of section 4.]`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank may buy and sell the`
  line `Central Government securities in the secondary market ^2[or converts Central Government Securities held`
  line `by it with other Securities of the Central Government as mutually agreed between the Reserve Bank and`
  line `the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 214, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 214, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4510)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Measures for fiscal transparency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4510&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall take suitable measures to`
  line `ensure greater transparency in its fiscal operations in public interest and minimise as far as practicable,`
  line `secrecy in the preparation of the annual financial statement and demands for grants.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the Central`
  line `Government shall, at the time of presentation of annual financial statement and demands for grants, make`
  line `such disclosures and in such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4511)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Measures to enforce compliance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4511&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Minister-in-charge of the Ministry of Finance shall`
  line `review, ^1[on half-yearly basis], the trends in receipts and expenditure in relation to the budget and place`
  line `before both Houses of Parliament the outcome of such reviews.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Central Government shall prepare a monthly statement of its accounts.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever there is either shortfall in revenue or excess of expenditure over the ^3[prescribed levels]`
  line `during any period in a financial year, the Central Government shall take appropriate measures for`
  line `increasing revenue or for reducing the expenditure (including curtailing of the sums authorised to be paid`
  line `and applied from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India under any Act so as to provide for the`
  line `appropriation of such sums):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the expenditure charged on the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India under clause (3) of article 112 of the Constitution or to any other expenditure which is`
  line `required to be incurred under any agreement or contract or such other expenditure which cannot be`
  line `postponed or curtailed.`
  line
  line `(3)(a) Except as provided under this Act, no deviation in meeting the obligations cast on the Central`
  line `Government under this Act, shall be permissible without approval of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(b) Where, owing to unforeseen circumstances, any deviation is made in meeting the obligations cast`
  line `on the Central Government under this Act, the Minister-in-charge of the Ministry of Finance shall make a`
  line `statement in both Houses of Parliament explaining--`
  line
  line `(i) any deviation in meeting the obligations cast on the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) whether such deviation is substantial and relates to the actual or the potential budgetary`
  line `outcomes; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the remedial measures the Central Government proposes to take.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 215, ibid., for "every quarter" (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 215, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 215, ibid., for "pre-specified levels mentioned in the Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement and the rules made under`
  line `this Act" (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (4512)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Laying of review reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 149 (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4512&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Laying of review reports.--The Central Government may entrust the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India to review periodically as required, the compliance of the provisions of this Act`
  line `and such reviews shall be laid on the table of both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4513)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4513&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the annual targets to be specified under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the fiscal indicators to be prescribed for the purpose of sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) the expenditure indicators with specifications of underlying assumptions and risk involved`
  line `under clause (a) of sub-section (6A) of section 3;]`
  line
  line `(c) the forms of the Medium-term Fiscal Policy Statement,`
  line `^2[Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement,`
  line `Medium-term Expenditure Framework Statement] and Macro-economic Frame Work Statement`
  line `referred to in sub-section (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^3* * * *`
  line *
  line
  line `(d) the disclosures and form in which such disclosures shall be made under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `^4[(da) the level of short fall in revenue or excess of expenditure under sub-section (2) of section 7;]`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 150, ibid. (w. e. f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 150, ibid., for Fiscal Policy Strategy Statement (w.e.f. 28-5-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (ca) omitted by Act of 13 of 2018, s. 216 (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 216, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4514)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Rules to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4514&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid,`
  line `as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4515)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4515&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or any officer of the Central Government for anything which is in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4516)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4516&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to question the`
  line `legality of any action taken by, or any decision of, the Central Government, under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4517)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4517&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4518)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918&sectionId=4518&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00031_200339_1517807322918
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
